CWC.DE.summary: CEWE Stiftung & Co. KGaA engages in photofinishing and commercial online printing businesses in germany. The company operates through Photofinishing, Retail, Commercial Online Printing, and Other Activities segments. It offers photos and photo books; wall art, such as posters, hard foam panels, canvas collages, on acrylic, and aluminium dibond or sophisticated gallery prints; calendars; greeting cards and folded cards or postcards; instant photos; and photo gifts, including photo mugs, wall clocks, t-shirts, and phone and tablet cases. The company also provides online printing services for flyers, posters, brochures, business cards, stationery, packaging, promotional items, etc. under the saxoprint, CEWE-PRINT.de, viaprinto.de, and Laserline brands. In addition, it is involved in walk-in stores and online shops that offers cameras, lenses, and accessories, as well as engages in the real estate property business. It operates approximately 147 stores. The company was founded in 1961 and is headquartered in Oldenburg, Germany.

JTH.MU.summary: Gesundheitswelt Chiemgau AG, together with its subsidiaries, provides health and wellness services in Germany. It operates clinics for orthopedic treatment and rehabilitation, geriatric rehabilitation, psychosomatic hospital treatment, oncology and cardiology, psychosomatic hospital treatment, and psychosomatics and psychotherapy; center of sports and rehabilitation diagnostics; and ambulatory and outpatient rehabilitation and health centers. The company was formerly known as Jod-Thermalbad Endorf AG and changed its name to Gesundheitswelt Chiemgau AG in July 2003. The company was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Bad Endorf, Germany. Gesundheitswelt Chiemgau AG is a subsidiary of Stiftung 'gesundheitswelt Chiemgau' Bad Endorf Gmbh.
